    <p>Vitauthority addresses the primary limitation of oral glutathione supplementation — bioavailability — with their liposomal delivery system. Standard oral glutathione is partially degraded by digestive enzymes and gastric acid before it reaches the intestinal lining for absorption. Liposomal encapsulation wraps the glutathione molecule within a phospholipid bilayer that mimics the structure of cell membranes, protecting it through the digestive tract and facilitating direct absorption into the bloodstream. A 2015 European Journal of Nutrition study found that liposomal glutathione increased blood GSH levels by 40% more than standard glutathione at equivalent doses.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>The bioavailability advantage of liposomal glutathione is particularly relevant for skin brightening applications. Since the <strong>skin-brightening mechanism requires sustained blood glutathione levels</strong> to continuously inhibit tyrosinase activity, the enhanced absorption of liposomal delivery may produce <strong>faster and more consistent results</strong> than standard forms — though head-to-head skin outcome studies are still needed.</p>
      <cite>Sinha et al., European Journal of Nutrition, 2015</cite>
    </div>

